Main Program: poetry.c
Compilation: gcc -ansi poetry.c -o poetry
Execution: ./poetry
About this program:
	The program will ask the user oto provide lines from a poem as input. This input can be any form of string as long as the line is less than 500 characters (Defined by the macro named MAXSIZE). The program only stops when the user enters a single period (.) or if the maximum number of lines (also defined by MAXSIZE) has been reached. 
Input: Lines from a poem
Output:
	# words on # lines
	# #...#(Number of words on each line)
